{
  "_id": "fhSubIronHour001",
  "name": "Ironhour Caps",
  "type": "consumable",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "folder": "fhSubModern00001",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Sealed glass vials of black-coated capsules sold under counter as \"jobsite supplements.\" The label is a knockoff of a defunct legitimate brand. Used by movers, longshoremen, and the desperate.</p><p><strong><em>Desired effects on use.</em></strong> For 1 hour you have advantage on Strength (Athletics) checks and your carrying capacity is doubled.</p><p><strong><em>On use, save against addiction.</em></strong> Make a DC 13 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, you gain the Addicted condition from Ironhour Caps (see below).</p><p><strong><em>Addicted from Ironhour Caps.</em></strong> While you have this Addicted condition, you are also Poisoned and have disadvantage on Dexterity saving throws (your reflexes feel a half-second slow).</p><p><strong><em>Withdrawal Modifier: 3.</em></strong> Withdrawal lasts max(3 &minus; your Constitution modifier, 2) long rests, minimum 1.</p><p><em>Requires: Vial.</em></p>"
    },
